asusctl (6.3.8-4~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Fix Launchpad build: Launchpad chroots have no internet access, so the
    rustup-via-curl approach in override_dh_auto_configure is broken.
  * Patch vendor/toml/Cargo.toml at build time (edition="2024"→"2021") and
    recalculate its cargo checksum inline — cargo 1.75 cannot parse edition
    2024 manifests even for excluded crates.
  * Remove curl, ca-certificates from Build-Depends (unused).

 -- Baraka Malila <bmalila87@gmail.com>  Sat, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

asusctl (6.3.8-3~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Add python3, curl, ca-certificates to Build-Depends.
  * Install cargo >=1.85 via rustup at configure time: vendor/toml uses
    edition="2024" which apt cargo 1.75 cannot parse.
  * Export CARGO_HOME and prepend ~/.cargo/bin to PATH in debian/rules.

 -- Baraka Malila <bmalila87@gmail.com>  Sat, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

asusctl (6.3.8-2~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Fix offline Launchpad build failures:
    - Skip upstream make distclean (override_dh_auto_clean) to preserve
      the vendored crates shipped in the orig tarball.
    - Lower Build-Depends rustc floor from 1.82 to 1.75 and pass
      --ignore-rust-version to cargo build.
    - Strip stale Cargo.toml.orig references from vendor checksums at
      build time (cargo vendor creates them; quilt cleanup deletes them).
    - Capture full cargo vendor stdout as .cargo/config.toml so that
      git-sourced dependencies are also redirected offline.
    - Add 0004-rust-version-floor.patch to lower workspace rust-version.

 -- Baraka Malila <bmalila87@gmail.com>  Sat, 05 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

